1. Difference between QA and QC.

QA (Quality Assurance) and QC (Quality Control) are both essential parts of software testing,
but they focus on different aspects.

Quality Assurance (QA):
QA is a process-oriented approach that focuses on preventing defects.

Quality Control (QC):
QC is a product-oriented approach that focuses on identifying defects.


Feature :         	QA (Quality Assurance)     	QC (Quality Control)
Focus	                Process	                         Product
Goal	              Prevent defects                	Detect defects
Approach	          Proactive	                        Reactive
Responsibility     	Entire team	                     Testing team
Activities	        Process improvement	             Testing & bug detection
Example	            Defining standards	              Running test cases

2.Explain in detail about STLC.

STLC (Software Testing Life Cycle):
     STLC is a structured process followed by testers to ensure software quality.

Phases of STLC:

1. Requirement Analysis:
* Understand business requirements
* Identify testable requirements
* Prepare RTM (Requirement Traceability Matrix).

2. Test Planning:
* Define testing strategy
* Estimate time, cost, and resources
* Select tools
* Deliverable: Test Plan Document

3. Test Case Design (Test Development)
* Write test cases and test scripts
* Prepare test data
* Review test cases

4. Test Environment Setup
* Prepare hardware and software setup
* Install required tools
* Ensure environment is ready for testing
5. Test Execution
* Execute test cases
* Report defects (bugs)
* Retest and perform regression testing
6. Test Closure
* Evaluate test completion criteria
* Prepare Test Summary Report
* Document lessons learned
